etymology.description: Variant form of 卅(卅) (sà, "thirty") -> repetition of 十(十) (shí, "ten") three times -> three tens = generation
etymology.interpretation: The character 丗 is a variant form of 卅(卅) (sà, "thirty"), which itself represents the number thirty by repeating the character for ten three times. This repetition symbolizes a group or generation made up of ten repeated thrice.
